gomodel:SYNGO_2112  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: the effects of the NEEP21 and GRIP1 interaction are tested via the ND overexpression of the interaction domains of the respective proteins (NEEP21 aa129164, GRIP1 aa8101112). NEEP21 aa129164 overexpression causes a reduction of Glur2 (but not Glur1) surface delivery after NDMA-induced AMPAR internalization (Fig.4). A similar observation was made with OE of ND GRIP1 aa8101112. OE of NEEP21 aa129164 does not lead to a general perturbatio of the endoctic pathways as assesed by recycling of transferrin (Fig.4G). The infusion of NEEP21 aa129164 is shown to change EPSC properties (changed current/voltage relationships) under basal conditions. The OE of NEEP21 aa129164 results in endosomal accumulation of AMPARs (Fig.7).\n\nnote; referenced PMID:16037816 shows the M&M for (confocal) microscopy. Experimental description: Supplementary materials cite Steiner et al 2002 as the source for the cDNA construct, and Steiner et al. 2002 (PMID:12070131) clone MOUSE Neep21/Nsg1" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2112" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

